description:
Origin

A man who chose to enlist as a Magistrate to subvert mutants into slaves.

Creation

Written by Chris Claremont and drawn by Rick Leonardi.

Major Story Arcs

Magistrates are sent out to recover a stolen flying craft. One Magistrate, Mollo, attempts to jump aboard the vessel but gets blown off. Cholly catches him with a safety line and begins to carry him to safety. DeKooning is tasked with flying under Mollo to catch him in case the safety line snaps.
name: DeKooning

deck: Commander of the Spartax Royal Guard and daughter of Emperor J-Son. She is Star Lord's half-sister.
description:
Origin

Victoria is the illegitimate daughter of the ruler of the Spartoi, J'son of Spartax. As she was not of full royal blood and of darker skin tone, she was treated as such.

Despite her father turning his back on her, Victoria remains loyal to Spartax. After J'son is desposed by his son Star-Lord, Victoria takes command of the Royal Guard to protect the millions of refugees after the Spartoi Empire began to crumble.

She planned to capture her half-brother to collect the bounty on his head and fund her troops, but he was able to convince her to double-cross the bounty collectors and steal their assets.

In Other Media

Television

Marvel's Guardians of the Galaxy

Victoria appears in the animated series, voiced by Cree Summer. Like in the comics, she is Star-Lord's younger sister and the captain of the Royal Guard.

description:
A businesswoman from the Midwest, Grace Valentine arrives at New York Beat magazine to talk about her feature on "the power and potential of the individual." However, she is shocked to find out her article is being bumped by a different piece all about Carol Danvers. She returns to her hotel room where she meets with her partner Richard. They discuss her cell phone app, and Richard reveals to her that he knows it also secretly collects personal data from its users. Richard threatens to report her to the authorities, but Valentine knocks him out with a lamp.

Later, Mayor J. Jonah Jameson is presiding over a ceremony to honor Carol Danvers with the Key to the City of New York in return for her work saving the city. Valentine attacks Carol with military drones that she has hacked into. She beams a live video feed of herself onto screens around Times Square, revealing Carol's alien nature and her history of alcoholism and her recent brain damage. However, the ordinary people of New York respond by standing alongside Carol to confuse the drones, which Carol proceeds to destroy. Valentine escapes, planning to disappear for a time.
